Minimalistic UI/UX Ruleset for React Projects
1. Layout & Structure

Use flex or grid for all layouts — never absolute positioning unless required.

Maintain a maximum page width of 1200px for readability.

Use consistent spacing units (4, 8, 16, 24, 32px) across the entire UI.

Keep components modular — 1 component = 1 responsibility.

2. Typography

Define two font sizes for body text: 14px and 16px.

Keep headings consistent: h1, h2, h3 with fixed scale (e.g., 32–24–18).

Limit fonts to one family + weight variations (no more than 3 weights).

3. Color System

Stick to one primary, one secondary, and one neutral palette.

Use opacity (e.g., rgba(0,0,0,0.05)) for borders/shadows instead of random colors.

Maintain a single accent color for CTAs.

4. Components

Every component must:

Accept className for overrides.

Be fully controlled or fully uncontrolled, never mixed.

Avoid internal styling unless necessary — prefer a consistent system (CSS modules, Tailwind, or styled-components).

5. Icons & Media

Keep icons thin-lined and consistent (Lucide, Heroicons).

Avoid icons > 24px.

Compress images before using them.

Assume dark mode from day one — choose colors that survive it.

6. Animations

Keep animations subtle: 150–250ms, ease-out.

Apply motion only to:

Buttons (hover)

Modals (fade+slide)

Dropdowns

No infinite loops or distracting movements.

7. Responsiveness

Start with mobile-first (min 360px width).

Use three breakpoints only:

sm: 640px

md: 768px

lg: 1024px

Hide non-essential UI on mobile.

8. Forms

Inputs must always have:

visible label

placeholder

error state

success/neutral state

Buttons must be:

full-width on mobile

have consistent border-radius (8–12px max)

9. State & Logic

Prefer React Query for async logic.

Keep component state minimal:

UI State → component

Session/user state → context

Server data → React Query

Avoid passing props more than 2 levels deep → use context or store.

10. Code Hygiene

Every file max 200 lines.

One component per file.

Use clear names:

Components: RecipeCard.jsx

Hooks: useFetchRecipe.js

Utils: formatCalories.js

Avoid anonymous functions in JSX if performance matters.

